import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['date'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['rate'])
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rate across all industries from 2000 to 2010?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'series'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    years = data['year'].unique()
    for year in years:
        year_data = data[data['year'] == year]
        max_rate = year_data['rate'].max()
        max_series = year_data[year_data['rate'] == max_rate]['series'].values[0]
        plt.bar(max_series, max_rate, color='red')
        plt.bar(year_data['series'], year_data['rate'], alpha=0.5)
        plt.axhline(max_rate, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Rate: {max_rate:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in a given year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["rate"].median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['month'] == i]['rate'] for i in range(1, 13)], labels=[i for i in range(1, 13)])
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_title('How does the unemployment rate vary across different months of a year?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['count'], data['rate'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Number of Unemployed People')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["count"].median():.2f}')
    ax.axhline(data['rate'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["rate"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of unemployed people and the unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
